32#ifndef _LINUX_IDR_H_
33#define _LINUX_IDR_H_
34
35#include <sys/types.h>
36#include <sys/rbtree.h>
37
38#include <linux/gfp.h>
39
40/* XXX Stupid expedient algorithm should be replaced by something better. */
41
42struct idr {
43 kmutex_t idr_lock;
44 rb_tree_t idr_tree;
45};
46
47/* XXX Make the nm output a little more greppable... */
48#define idr_alloc linux_idr_alloc
49#define idr_destroy linux_idr_destroy
50#define idr_find linux_idr_find
51#define idr_for_each linux_idr_for_each
52#define idr_get_next linux_idr_get_next
53#define idr_init linux_idr_init
54#define idr_is_empty linux_idr_is_empty
55#define idr_preload linux_idr_preload
56#define idr_preload_end linux_idr_preload_end
57#define idr_remove linux_idr_remove
58#define idr_replace linux_idr_replace
59
60int linux_idr_module_init(void);
61void linux_idr_module_fini(void);
62
63void idr_init(struct idr *);
64void idr_destroy(struct idr *);
65bool idr_is_empty(struct idr *);
66void *idr_find(struct idr *, int);
67void *idr_get_next(struct idr *, int *);
68void *idr_replace(struct idr *, void *, int);
69void idr_remove(struct idr *, int);
70void idr_preload(gfp_t);
71int idr_alloc(struct idr *, void *, int, int, gfp_t);
72void idr_preload_end(void);
73int idr_for_each(struct idr *, int (*)(int, void *, void *), void *);
74
75#define idr_for_each_entry(IDR, ENTRY, ID) \
76 for ((ID) = 0; ((ENTRY) = idr_get_next((IDR), &(ID))) != NULL; (ID)++)
77
78struct ida {
79 struct idr ida_idr;
80};
81
82static inline void
83ida_init(struct ida *ida)
84{
85
86 idr_init(&ida->ida_idr);
87}
88
89static inline void
90ida_destroy(struct ida *ida)
91{
92
93 idr_destroy(&ida->ida_idr);
94}
95
96static inline void
97ida_remove(struct ida *ida, int id)
98{
99
100 idr_remove(&ida->ida_idr, id);
101}
102
103static inline int
104ida_simple_get(struct ida *ida, unsigned start, unsigned end, gfp_t gfp)
105{
106 int id;
107
108 KASSERT(start <= INT_MAX);
109 KASSERT(end <= INT_MAX);
110
111 idr_preload(gfp);
112 id = idr_alloc(&ida->ida_idr, NULL, start, end, gfp);
113 idr_preload_end();
114
115 return id;
116}
117
118static inline void
119ida_simple_remove(struct ida *ida, unsigned int id)
120{
121
122 KASSERT((int)id >= 0);
123 ida_remove(ida, id);
124}
125
126#endif /* _LINUX_IDR_H_ */
